q("php-47", "What is the difference between session and cookie?", ["Session data stored on server; cookies stored on client", "No difference", "Cookies are more secure", "Session is for files only"], 0, "Sessions store data server-side with a session ID cookie; cookies store data directly on the client (browser).");
q("php-48", "How do you set a cookie that expires in 1 hour?", ["setcookie('name', 'value', time()+3600);", "makecookie('name', 'value', 3600);", "cookie_set('name', 'value', '+1 hour');", "set_cookie('name', 'value', 3600);"], 0, "setcookie() takes a Unix timestamp as the expiration time. time()+3600 adds 1 hour (3600 seconds) from now.");
